The 2022 Oscars were comprised of 23 award categories that were spread out over the night. A number more were aired before the official ceremony began, as well. While Dune was a hot favourite, it had quite a line-up of movies to go up against. Disney also had great stakes in the awards with Encanto vying for Best Animated Feature. Meanwhile, Will Smith was up for Best Actor, despite the fact he literally hit someone on stage. Scroll down for the full list of nominees and winners. Coda – Winner Belfast Don’t Look Up Drive My Car Dune King Richard Licorice Pizza Nightmare Alley The Power of the Dog West Side Story Jane Campion (The Power of the Dog) – Winner Kenneth Branagh (Belfast) Drive My Car (Ryûsuke Hamaguchi) Paul Thomas Anderson (Licorice Pizza) Steven Spielberg (West Side Story) Jessica Chastain (The Eyes of Tammy Faye) – Winner Olivia Colman (The Lost Daughter) Penélope Cruz (Parallel Mothers) Nicole Kidman (Being the Ricardos) Kristen Stewart (Spencer) Will Smith (King Richard) – Winner Javier Bardem (Being the Ricardos) Benedict Cumberbatch (The Power of the Dog) Andrew Garfield (tick, tick … BOOM!) Denzel Washington (The Tragedy of Macbeth) Best Supporting Actress Ariana DeBose (West Side Story) – Winner Jessie Buckley (The Lost Daughter) Judi Dench (Belfast) Kirsten Dunst (The Power of the Dog) Aunjanue Ellis (King Richard) Troy Kotsur (Coda) – Winner Ciarán Hinds (Belfast) Jesse Plemons (The Power of the Dog) JK Simmons (Being the Ricardos) Kodi Smit-McPhee (The Power of the Dog) Dune – Winner Don’t Look Up Encanto Parallel Mothers The Power of the Dog Dune – Winner Nightmare Alley The Power of the Dog The Tragedy of Macbeth West Side Story Drive My Car – Winner Flee The Hand of God Lunana: A Yak in the Classroom The Worst Person in the World Dune – Winner Nightmare Alley The Power of the Dog The Tragedy of Macbeth West Side Story Dune – Winner Free Guy Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings No Time to Die Spider-Man: No Way Home Dune – Winner Don’t 